SIMPLE: exchangeable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exchangeable
<hw>Ex*change"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧changeable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being
exchanged; fit or proper to be exchanged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The officers captured with Burgoyne were <qex>exchangeable</qex>
within the powers of General Howe.</q> <rj><qau>Marshall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Available for making exchanges; ratable.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>exchangeable</xex> value.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. S.
Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exchangeably</ent>⟦br⟧
